tspan.tspan: To reconcile this paradox, we should
consider what truth really is, as our
current everyday notion of it is obviously
wrong - truth does not exist in the
world, truth is subjective. Reality is like
a canvas that contains the form of the
world, but it is up to the observer, to us,
to draw the contours: we circle one spot
and say "This is A". Then we take
another picture and search for where A
